This paper deals with the sharing of spectrum among different tiers of users, which is a topic that falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also uses game theory to analyze the competition between different types of users, which falls under the category of Game Theory and Economics (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the role of Environmental Sensing Capability operators in monitoring spectrum occupancy, which could be classified under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) or Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
